{"TopicId":151189,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Why Kerbin is so small compared to Earth","CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:18:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:18:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just wonder why Kerbin is so small. Also don\u0027t get me started on Gilly because that must be so small. But Why not the size of Earth or what not? Eh I don\u0027t really care on size anyways. But I still wonder.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:huh:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:huh:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:26:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the size of a planet affects delta-v requirements for orbit more than its gravity, so a smaller planet makes a easier game. \u00A0There are earth sized planet rescale mods that you can try to see for yourself. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:28:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477877178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mad Rocket Scientist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Mad Rocket Scientist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the size of a planet affects delta-v requirements for orbit more than its gravity, so a smaller planet makes a easier game. \u00A0There are earth sized planet rescale mods that you can try to see for yourself. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait! But the real question is DUN DUN\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;DOES IT WORK WITH MECHJEB!\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DD_bwest","CreatedById":164906,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:29:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIve always thought, and i could be very wrong on this, it has to do with gameplay.\u00A0\u00A0 getting into a real earth orbit takes longer, so it requires more patience.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni would imagine if it was scaled up to earth size, the rest would sorta have to match.\u00A0 which means longer burns again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:30:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477877385\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164906\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DD_bwest\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, DD_bwest said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIve always thought, and i could be very wrong on this, it has to do with gameplay.\u00A0\u00A0 getting into a real earth orbit takes longer, so it requires more patience.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni would imagine if it was scaled up to earth size, the rest would sorta have to match.\u00A0 which means longer burns again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood point\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477877178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mad Rocket Scientist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Mad Rocket Scientist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause the size of a planet affects delta-v requirements for orbit more than its gravity, so a smaller planet makes a easier game. \u00A0There are earth sized planet rescale mods that you can try to see for yourself. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere can i get this mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlphaMensae","CreatedById":152463,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:38:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, it was a design decision by KSP\u0027s creator, Felipe (HarvesteR, now moved on), to have a 1/10 scale solar system so it would be simpler and easier for rocketry newcomers.\u00A0The delta-V requirements are so much less, and fuel tanks and engines don\u0027t have to have realistic specifications.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/50471-113-real-solar-system-v1140-july-3/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EReal Solar System\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0turns the stock fictional 1/10 size solar system into the actual full-sized one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-31T01:39:03Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2016 01:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Laguna\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:43:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831205\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477877920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152463\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laguna\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Laguna said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(HarvesteR, now moved on)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat do you mean \u003Cimg alt=\u0022-_-\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_sleep.png\u0022 title=\u0022-_-\u0022\u003E\u00A0DO YOU MEAN HE DIED NOOOOOOOOOOOOO\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AlphaMensae","CreatedById":152463,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:46:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831213\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477878211\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169331\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Program Kerbal Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Program Kerbal Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat do you mean \u003Cimg alt=\u0022-_-\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_sleep.png\u0022 title=\u0022-_-\u0022\u003E\u00A0DO YOU MEAN HE DIED NOOOOOOOOOOOOO\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, he\u0027s still alive, just moved on from KSP to something else, i.e. left Squad. Poor choice of words, I guess.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Program Kerbal Space","CreatedById":169331,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T01:47:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831214\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477878399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152463\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laguna\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Laguna said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, he\u0027s still alive, just moved on from KSP to something else, i.e. left Squad. Poor choice of words, I guess.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYAY hes safe\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T02:28:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222831192\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151189\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477877443\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169331\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Program Kerbal Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, Program Kerbal Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[...]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere can i get this mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is realism overhaul, meant to fully simulate real life rocket science. \u00A0All real planets are in this, at full size:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/140070-113-realism-overhaul-v1132-august-31/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is real solar system, which turns the kerbol system into the real solar system, but does not change anything else. \u00A0AFAIK, pretty hard without realism overhaul too, as stock mass fractions are quite low.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/50471-113-real-solar-system-v1140-july-3/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can adjust said mass fractions with SMURFF to more realistic levels for use with real solar system:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/117992-12-smurff-simple-module-adjustments-for-real-ish-fuel-mass-fractions-155-02016-oct-29/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, and there\u0027s this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138572-wip-113-203-stock-size-real-solar-system/\u0026amp;page=1\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReal planets at a stock size.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-31T02:29:46Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2016 02:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Mad Rocket Scientist\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T10:31:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin was made before there timewarp was implemented, its smaller size allows 30 minute orbits compared to the 90 minute ones for an Earth-like planet. Most everything else was scaled from there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}